My current plan is to OCaml-ize the Nebula2 3D engine.
http://nebuladevice.cubik.org  Nebula2 is a commercial quality engine
and has a MIT-style license.  A lot needs to happen to create value add
over and above C++.  So I thought I would ask you people, what would
your ideal OCaml 3D engine do?   Ignore for a moment that I'm working on
a legacy C++ codebase and pretend I'm some super-wizard who can do
anything you want from scratch (short of free tickets to Disneyland.
:-)  What would make an OCaml, functionally programmed 3D engine greatly
superior to other product offerings out there?

